The paper focuses on the initialization of parameters in deep neural network models for classification problems, specifically using multinomial logistic regression. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a closed-form approximate solution for logistic regression and discusses its properties, indicating that it may also be relevant to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper applies its approach to image classification and object detection tasks, which suggests that it may also be relevant to Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) for tasks such as text classification.
